data.meta_description: Nathan Douglas, son of David and Waite (Hawkes) Douglas, was born in Durham 18 Jan 1812.  He married 2 Oct 1834 Lucy, daughter of Isaiah and Deborah (Philbrook) Day.    He began preaching among the Friends at the age of 22 and was for half a century the principal minister of the Friends in Durham.   Source:  History of...
